    Kenneth Tangerois3 Maroca year ago on Google
    5/5
    Le Mirage is an exceptional five-star hotel that began several decades ago as a simple cafe and then expanded into the luxury hotel that it is today. The rooms and suites here are all of the upmost taste and quality as are the reception …
    Le Mirage is an exceptional five-star hotel that began several decades ago as a simple cafe and then expanded into the luxury hotel that it is today. The rooms and suites here are all of the upmost taste and quality as are the reception area and restaurant.
    The outside dining terrace is most pleasant with spectacular Sidi Kacem beach and Atlantic Ocean views. Le Mirage has a huge swimming pool with surrounding terraces for the pampered guests to enjoy during their stay.
    Since it first opened, Le Mirage has had its share of celebrities, including film stars, designers, aristocrats, dying despots and those who wish excellent food and luxurious lodgings in peaceful and beautiful oceanfront surroundings. They have a choice of suites-villas fit for a king.
    One afternoon, while acting as social secretary
    for a friend, having organized an extravagant indoor lunch for his 30 guests, I looked out on the terrace and spotted a famous French actor who I had always wanted to meet, but alas, I was too busy.
    The lunches, dinners and breakfasts are all very good and artistically presented. There is a traditional bar that was decorated with wall fabrics and antique furniture by a friend in the best traditional understated taste.
    You will find this one of the best places to stay or eat in Tangier. Le Mirage is located about 25 minutes by car or taxi from downtown Tangier and 10 minutes from Tangier's Ibn Batutta Airport.

    About this hotel

    A 2-minute walk from the legendary Caves of Hercules, this ornate cliffside hotel on landscaped grounds along the Atlantic Ocean is 11 km from both Tangier Ibn Batouta Airport and the Royal Golf de Tanger club. …

    Featuring furnished terraces with ocean views, the grand suites have Wi-Fi access, flat-screens, minibars and separate sitting areas; some provide marble floors and lavish bathrooms. Swanky villas add private pools. Room service is available.

    Amenities include an outdoor pool, and stair access to the shore, plus a ritzy restaurant, a gym and a terrace; all offer ocean views. There's also a plush piano bar with regular live music.
